<font color="#FF0000">MY FRIENDS</font><br>
<tt>Fri Sep  5 16:48:42 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
First, Silent Warrior, the lack of pain and all that associated with it is directly related to psychic numbing. I am sure you have heard that term before.  The site brought out to me that the rage (not anger) I was feeling was a mask over all my other emotions.  It is strictly a matter of control.  If I don't feel, it din't mean nuthin.  My wife never, I mean never saw tears from me in the first 20 years of our marriage.  She saw a lot of anger, nasty temper, frustration , but never tears.  I learned that if I cried I was out of control.  Tears are a release and there is no control.  If to extend this control issue; don't cry, stay in control.  I had that control and found out that controlling tears also limited my capacity to love, feel tenderness, care for someone and most of GRIEVE!!!  If you can't grieve for that which is lost, how can we ever expect to heal?<br>
It was the night of the dedication of the Statue of Liberty.. I never placed myself in front of a display of patriotism, but this captured me.. As I was watching this, tears rolled down my face, as they are now,  it was a start. It scared my wife to death, but she was glad, because she knew the healing had started.  So , Silent Warrior, Work this site like it is a lifeline... Get  info, advice, laughs, hurts, but share and heal. They all helped and they will come back.<br><br>
Tom, my friend,  I agree with you 100% that this site is a repository for history and information.  It is not often that people get the opportunity to speak to the participants of a historical event that changed the course of a nation.  There are threads for these in place. As there are threads for humor.  But if vets come here to read and post feelings, it should be a place to discuss issues and maybe help?  I am not proposing to save the world.  Just help some old farts like myself make the path a little easier.  Too lofty an ambition?  Maybe, but it can't hurt to try.
